steps.description:
There are two styles of gameplay for Nightblades. The first is a more combat-based style, where your Nightblade will be getting all up in the action and dealing damage to your enemies. If you want to do this style of gameplay, you'll want to focus on the skills in the Assassination tree (and to a lesser extent, the Siphoning tree). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/26/Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/26/Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":288,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":475,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Leaning towards dual-wield is also a good idea, as that does more damage than a bow and is intended for more face-to-face combat. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/18/Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/18/Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":288,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":475,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If taking this route, it might be a good idea to distribute some points to health, though the majority should still go towards magicka and stamina. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/90/Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-8Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-8Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/90/Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-8Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-8Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":288,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":475,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

The other style of gameplay is more stealth-based, where your Nightblade will avoid the bulk of the action in favor of distanced attacks and staying out of sight. If you want to do this style of gameplay, you'll want to focus on the skills in the Shadow tree (and to a lesser extent, the Siphoning tree). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/db/Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-9Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-9Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/db/Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-9Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-9Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":288,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":475,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Leaning towards bow use is also a good idea, since you'll want to be attacking from a distance and not up close. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e1/Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-9Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-9Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e1/Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-9Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-9Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":288,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":475,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If taking this route, it might be a good idea to distribute more points towards stamina than magicka, as magicka points do not regenerate while using your class abilities (which are mainly related to turning invisible, if you took our suggestion of the Shadow skill tree). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a2/Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-9Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-9Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a2/Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-9Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Play-a-Nightblade-in-Elder-Scrolls-Online-Step-9Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":288,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":475,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
